</style>

<div class="dcf-header">
  <div class="dcf-header-content">
    <div class="dcf-tag">Original Research</div>
    <h1>Cigna (CI)<br/>Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <p class="dcf-subtitle">A transparent, two-stage discounted cash flow valuation of The Cigna Group. Using the latest actuals, disclosed assumptions, and one final number.</p>
    <p class="dcf-date">Updated Today · Data: Latest Financials</p>
    <p class="dcf-compiled">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="dcf-wrapper">
  <!-- ═══ THE VERDICT ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-label">Estimated Intrinsic Value Per Share</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-vs">vs. market price of ${currentPrice.toFixed(2)} ({marginOfSafety}%)</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background: ${verdictColor}22; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}44;`}>
      {verdictText}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ KEY METRICS ═══ -->
  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(latestRev / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Latest Revenue</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Free Cash Flow</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{sharesOutstanding}M</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Shares Outstanding</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">{(latestOp / latestRev * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Operating Margin</div>
    </div>
    <div class="stat-card">
      <div class="stat-value">${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B</div>
      <div class="stat-label">Net Cash (Debt)</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY ═══ -->
  <h2>Methodology: Two-Stage DCF</h2>
  <p>We use a <strong>two-stage discounted cash flow (DCF)</strong> model — the gold standard of intrinsic valuation. No multiples, no comparables, no vibes. Just future cash flows discounted to today.</p>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">1</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Start with actual Free Cash Flow</h4>
      <p>Cigna generated <strong>${(fcfBase / 1000).toFixed(2)} billion</strong> in free cash flow recently. This is operating cash flow minus capital expenditures. This is real cash the business produces after paying for everything, including regulatory compliance and technology investments.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">2</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Project FCF growth for 5 years (Phase 1)</h4>
      <p>We grow FCF at <strong>{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}% per year</strong> for 5 years. This reflects a steady, mature growth profile expected from a major healthcare and PBM organization, balancing organic growth with margin pressures.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">3</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Calculate terminal value (Phase 2)</h4>
      <p>After Year 5, we assume FCF grows at <strong>{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}% forever</strong> — roughly GDP growth plus modest pricing power. We use the <strong>Gordon Growth Model</strong>: Terminal Value = FCF₆ ÷ (discount rate − terminal growth rate).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">4</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Discount everything to present value</h4>
      <p>All future cash flows are discounted at <strong>{(discountRate * 100)}%</strong> — our required rate of return. This is the cost of equity for a large-cap healthcare company, adequately above the 10Y Treasury (4.18%) to account for equity risk and regulatory uncertainty.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="method-step">
    <div class="step-num">5</div>
    <div class="step-content">
      <h4>Add net cash, divide by shares</h4>
      <p>Enterprise Value + Net Cash (${(netCash / 1000).toFixed(1)}B) = Equity Value. Divide by shares outstanding ({sharesOutstanding}M) for the per-share intrinsic value.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ THE THREE ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Three Assumptions That Drive Everything</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We're making exactly <strong>three</strong> judgment calls — everything else is math. Here's what we chose and why.</p>

  <div class="assumption-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">FCF Growth Rate (Years 1-5)</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        A balanced estimate for a massive, mature healthcare conglomerate. Cigna's Evernorth (PBM) business provides strong, steady cash flows, while the healthcare benefits side faces moderate margin pressure. 8% assumes consistent execution without hyper-growth.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Discount Rate (WACC)</div>
      <div class="value">{(discountRate * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        10Y Treasury: 4.18%. We use 10% — the rate most institutional investors use as a hurdle for large-cap equities. This provides a margin of safety against regulatory risks inherent in the US healthcare system.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="label">Terminal Growth Rate</div>
      <div class="value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100)}%</div>
      <div class="rationale">
        Long-term nominal GDP growth is ~3%. We add 0.5% for Cigna's structural advantages and the inherently inflationary nature of US healthcare costs, assuming they can maintain pricing power over time.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ FCF PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Projected Free Cash Flows</h2>
  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Year</th>
          <th>FCF ($M)</th>
          <th>PV Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value ($M)</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Base (Latest)</td>
          <td>${fcfBase.toLocaleString()}</td>
          <td>—</td>
          <td>—</td>
        </tr>
        {projectedFCF.map(p => (
          <tr>
            <td>Year {p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toLocaleString()}</td>
            <td>{p.pvFactor.toFixed(4)}</td>
            <td>${p.pvFCF.toLocaleString()}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td colspan="3">Sum of Phase 1 PV</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
